<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Eichstätt</head><p>Der Rat teilt Unkenntnis wegen Georg Römer, Bürger zu Eichstätt, mit und verweist diesen auf den Rechtsweg.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_203" id="101r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_203_r2l2">Rat cʒü <expan>Eyſt<ex>et</ex></expan> </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_203_r2l3"><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan> <expan>fr<ex>ewnde</ex></expan> / Als Jr vns <expan>v<ex>er</ex>ſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von <expan>Görg<ex>en</ex></expan> Römers <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_203_r2l4"><expan>mitburg<ex>er</ex>s</expan> <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> / <expan>Laſſ<ex>en</ex></expan> wir ewr frewntſchaft vviſſen / daʒ </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_203_r2l5">wir vormals davon nicht gehört <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> / vnd als er <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan> ſein </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_203_r2l7">recht dafür getan hat / wollen wir Jn der ſache 
<add><ab facs="#facs_203_r2l6">auch </ab></add> <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> verwiſſen </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_203_r2l8">vnd wo wir ew lıeb vnd <expan>fruntſch<ex>aft</ex></expan> <expan>beweıſ<ex>en</ex></expan> <expan>möht<ex>en</ex></expan> das <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_203_r2l9"><expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> / <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> <expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> ıj̃ . <expan>p<ex>oſt</ex></expan> Thome <expan>Ap<ex>oſto</ex>lı</expan> . </ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_203" id="101r"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Rat czü <expan>Eyst<ex>et</ex></expan>
</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieben</ex></expan>
<expan>fr<ex>eunde</ex></expan>, als ir uns
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>schr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt von
                                <expan>Görg<ex>en</ex></expan> Römers, <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan>
<expan>mitburg<ex>er</ex>s</expan>, <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>,
                                <expan>lass<ex>en</ex></expan> wir ewr frewntschaft wissen, daz wir
                        vormals davon nicht gehört <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>; und als er
                                <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan> sein recht dafür getan hat, wollen wir
                        in der sache <add>auch</add>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan> verwissen. Und wo wir ew lieb und
                                <expan>fruntsch<ex>aft</ex></expan>
<expan>beweis<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>möht<ex>en</ex></expan>, das <expan>tet<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                                <expan>g<ex>er</ex>ne</expan>. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> ii <expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan> Thome
                                <expan>ap<ex>osto</ex>li</expan>. </ab>
</div>
</div></body>
